<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-convert-between-pixels-and-degrees">=
Convert Between Pixels and Degrees</h2>



<p>A very useful online visual angle calculator that converts between pixel=
s and degrees. The perfect tool for figuring out the size of your stimuli, =
where to position objects in your eye-tracking task, or how far away your s=
creen should be. Enter your screen resolution, dimensions, and distance on =
the left, then choose the appropriate tab on the right. Use =E2=80=9CCenter=
ed=E2=80=9D for objects centered on the screen (or the screen itself). Use =
=E2=80=9COne Sided=E2=80=9D to compute the distance of objects (e.g. target=
s in saccade tasks) from the screen center. Use =E2=80=9COff Center=E2=80=
=9D to compute the size of objects that are offset from the screen center. =
Enter degrees of visual angle or pixels on the right =E2=80=93 the app conv=
erts from pixels to degrees and from degrees to pixels. You can find out mo=
re about how the calculator works in <a href=3D"https://www.sr-research.com=
/eye-tracking-blog/background/visual-angle/"><strong>this blog</strong>.</a=
></p>



